"title": "5354: invasions",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5354: invasions",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A hostile incursion into the territory of another tribe or nation, often with the object of its permanent annexation.</p>\n<h2>The Israelites' invasion of Canaan</h2>\n<h3>Their success had been preordained</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:22\">DEU 7:22</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:23-Lev20:24\">LEV 20:23–20:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:25\">EXO 12:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:34\">LEV 14:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:10\">LEV 23:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:10-Deut6:12\">DEU 6:10–6:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:17-Deut7:24\">DEU 7:17–7:24</a></p>\n<h3>Moses gave instructions on how to proceed</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:1-Deut7:5\">DEU 7:1–7:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut20:10-Deut20:20\">DEU 20:10–20:20</a></p>\n<h3>Joshua followed Moses in leading the invasion</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh11:23\">JOS 11:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh6:20\">JOS 6:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh8:18-Josh8:19\">JOS 8:18–8:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh10:29-Josh10:43\">JOS 10:29–10:43</a></p>\n<h3>The invasion continued under other leaders</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg1:4\">JDG 1:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg4:23-Judg4:24\">JDG 4:23–4:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg11:21-Judg11:22\">JDG 11:21–11:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg11:32-Judg11:33\">JDG 11:32–11:33</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs3:24\">2KI 3:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr4:41-1Chr4:43\">1CH 4:41–4:43</a></p>\n<h2>Invasion of the Israelites' land</h2>\n<h3>By the Philistines</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg10:6-Judg10:10\">JDG 10:6–10:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr14:9\">1CH 14:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr21:16-2Chr21:17\">2CH 21:16–21:17</a></p>\n<h3>By other nations</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:3-Judg6:5\">JDG 6:3–6:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg2:14\">JDG 2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs13:20\">2KI 13:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:1\">2CH 20:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr24:23\">2CH 24:23</a></p>\n<h3>Israel taken into captivity by Assyrian invaders</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:5-2Kgs17:6\">2KI 17:5–17:6</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:9-2Kgs18:11\">2KI 18:9–18:11</a></p>\n<h3>Judah taken into captivity by Babylonian invaders</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:1\">2KI 25:1</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer39:1\">JER 39:1</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:10-2Kgs25:11\">2KI 25:10–25:11</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer39:8-Jer39:9\">JER 39:8–39:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer52:4\">JER 52:4</a></p>\n<h2>Invasion of the promised land was a cause of great sadnesss</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps79:1\">PSA 79:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:1-Neh1:4\">NEH 1:1–1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam1:1-Lam1:3\">LAM 1:1–1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:4-Dan9:6\">DAN 9:4–9:6</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of non-human invasion</h2>\n<h3>By locusts</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod10:14\">EXO 10:14</a></strong></p>\n<h3>By evil spiritual forces</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:43-Matt12:45\">MAT 12:43–12:45</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:24-Luke11:26\">LUK 11:24–11:26</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:3\">LUK 22:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:17-Mark9:18\">MRK 9:17–9:18</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:14-Matt17:16\">MAT 17:14–17:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:38-Luke9:40\">LUK 9:38–9:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:12-Rom5:14\">ROM 5:12–5:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:12\">EPH 6:12</a></p>",
